Description: [Tekening FG in potlood].[recto] 'The Deluge', Panel, 9 3/4 x 17 3/4 inches, ex. Masing Coll. Vienna. Certificates by Friedländer (A'dam 15-2-54) & Valentiner (Los Angeles Jan. 16, 55): Pieter Bruegel the Elder; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. Not P.B.I, does not fit, into any of his periods. A certain relation to the engraved small landscapes series does not prove Bruegel's authorship; [verso] as these are not by Bruegel. Above all the vedute character speaks against P.B. It is a work derived from him, the landscape silhouette or the horizon to be compared with Winterlandscape with Bird Trap. The stressing of the white speak against P. Bruegel. The trees are coarse when in my view correspond with his. It is the work of a close follower of Bruegel. The fine painting of the ducks so different from P.B. birds, might possibly indicate Jan Brueghel the Younger, but cf. also Jacob Grimmer, Village Street, fully signed and dated 1583 (or 1589) De Boer Exh. 1934, N° 128 (pl. 18). Photograph shown by Hallsborough 17-7-57.[scan]
